			"contents": "科学史和技术史，对于科学教育而言有着不可低估的作用。\n\n但是，目前人们对于科学史已经比较重视了。但是，对于技术史还不够。\n\n这一点，可以从教科书中看到。\n\n为什么，要重视技术发展史呢？因为，科学史对应的是科学发现，而技术发展史对应的是技术创新和发明。\n\n重视技术发展史，不仅能够揭示创新的机制和情境，还能帮助学生认识科学与技术、技术与社会之间的紧密关系。\n\n这方面的研究，可以从教科书开始。事物进化需要从简单到复杂，科技发明也有其发展过程。\n\n技术发展史与科学史的区别，在于科学是发现，技术是发明，科学丰富人类认知，技术增强人类改造自然的能力，但是技术试一把双刃剑，它在赋予人类能力的同时带来了不可预知的风险。使得人类进入了风险化社会。\n\n\n\n\n\nIn the present study, the correlated seven-factor structure was examined based on the SSTCEAS upon which the ALI was developed. The seven factors including their corresponding items are as follows:\n(a) Choosing assessment methods appropriate for instructional decisions (items 1, 8, 15, 22 and 29);\n\n(b) Developing assessment methods appropriate for instructional decisions (items 2, 9, 16, 23 and 30);\n\n(c) Administering, scoring, and interpreting assessment results (items 3, 10, 17, 24 and 31);\n\n(d) Using assessment results when making decisions about individual students, planning teaching, developing curriculum, and school improvement (items 4, 11, 18, 25 and 32);\n\n(e) Developing valid grading procedures (items 5, 12, 19, 26 and 33);\n(f) Communicating assessment results to students, parents, lay audiences, and other educators (items 6, 13, 20, 27 and 34); and\n\n(g) Recognising unethical, illegal, and otherwise inappropriate use of assessment information (items 7, 14, 21, 28 and 35).\n",
